<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
" and "
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> t </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
" be the time periods of the motion in three parts of the motion as given in the question. Considering the first part of the motion,
</para>
<para id="element-46">
